message.content:
A notebook is a portable device for writing and taking notes, typically composed of many pages bound together.
The cover of a notebook can come in a variety of colors, ranging from solid colors to intricate designs.
Notebooks commonly have a texture on the cover, ranging from a smooth or glossy surface to a rough or bumpy texture.
The most common shape for a notebook is rectangular, with many different sizes available for different needs.
Notebooks can be found in many settings, including schools, offices, and homes as a tool for organization and note-taking.
Inside, the pages of a notebook are typically blank or lined to allow for writing or drawing.
Notebooks can be made from a variety of materials, including paper, recycled materials, or with a digital interface for electronic note-taking.
